text.section:
A licensed pharmacist may delegate pharmacy acts to a registered pharmacy technician, pharmacy student, or pharmacy technician trainee provided that the delegated pharmacy acts:
Are directly supervised by a licensed pharmacist;
Are not required to be performed by a licensed pharmacist;
Are within the education, training, experience, and area of practice of the delegating licensed pharmacist; and
Are appropriate to the education, training, and experience of the registered pharmacy technician, pharmacy student, or pharmacy technician trainee.
